Finals

[May 23]
Atletico  1-1  Cruzeiro

[May 26]
Atletico  0-0  Cruzeiro

[Jun 2]
Atletico  1-0  Cruzeiro           [Att: 19,681]
[Vaduca 84']

ATLeTICO: Zeca, William, Benito; Afonso, Hilton, Haroldo;
Murilinho, Vaduca, Tomazinho, Toledo, Amorim. Coach: Delio Neves.
CRUZEIRO: Genivaldo, Gerson, Vave; Adelino, Lazarotti, Pireco;
Pelau, Nilo, Gilberto, Guerino, Chiquinho. Coach: Ayrton Moreira.

Before the third match of the finals, Cruzeiro filed an action in the Minas Gerais Court of Sports (TJD)
requesting the points won by Atletico in the second match, claiming that Atletico player Laercio didn't
have some of the required personal documentations and thus his contract of registry with the club would
be invalid. In May 31, before the third match, the Minas Gerais Court of Sports decided by 6 votes to none
to reject Cruzeiro's filing, because the responsibility of this error was of Minas Gerais Football
Federation (FMF) and not of Atletico. In March 1959, Cruzeiro won this action in the Superior Court of Sports
(STJD) and the problem returned to FMF, who tried to schedule another match, but Atletico didn't accept it
because the two teams have changed many players ever since. Therefore, FMF has decided to solve the problem
by proclaiming both teams champions.

*** ATLeTICO and CRUZEIRO are Minas Gerais state champions of 1956 ***

